{"word":"H1330 - בְּתוּלָה - bᵉthûwlâh - beth-oo-law' - Maid","slug":"H1330","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">בְּתוּלָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>bᵉthûwlâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>beth-oo-law'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Maid"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D1;&#x05BC;&#x05EA;&#x05D5;&#x05BC;&#x05DC;&#x05D4; - b<sup>e</sup>thu&#x0302;la&#x0302;h</b> - <i>beth-oo-law'</i><p/>Feminine passive participle of an unused root meaning to <i>separate</i>; a <i>virgin</i> (from her <i>privacy</i>); sometimes (by continuation) a <i>bride</i>; also (figuratively) a <i>city</i> or <i>state: - </i>maid, virgin."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1331\">H1331</a>"}]}